Key Match Events: Pakistan defeated Ireland by six wickets in the third and final T20I to clinch the series 2-1
Pre-Game Insights: Pakistan have won the toss and opted to bowl first in the third T20I against Ireland in Dublin
Post-Match Reflections: Pakistan win with ease. The visiting team chase down Ireland's target of 179 runs with six wickets and 18 balls to spare, clinching the series by a 2-1 margin
Miscellaneous Highlights: Babar Azam and Co will now head to England to embark on a four-match T20I series, starting May 22
Others: Ireland have kept the run-scoring tempo up against Pakistan, piling on 125 runs for the loss of two wickets after 12.5 overs at the time of writing in the third T20I
